From 028b45bcb8cddbf23b95ccbf2de6f184d9387ae7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chronium Build <chronium@interlink.local>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 15:34:49 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 02/14] chronium: add Mojo plumbing browser->renderer for
 fingerprint config

Adds the Mojo channel that lets each renderer fetch the fingerprint
config that the browser singleton (patch 0001) loaded from JSON.

New mojom: chrome::mojom::FingerprintConfigProvider with one method
GetConfig() returning chrome::mojom::FingerprintConfig (seed only
for now; later patches will extend the struct as they need fields).

Browser side: FingerprintProfile now implements
FingerprintConfigProvider directly and exposes a static Bind() that
PopulateChromeFrameBinders registers per RenderFrameHost. Receivers
are kept in a ReceiverSet on the singleton.

Renderer side: ChromeRenderFrameObserver::DidCreateNewDocument
issues GetConfig() through the BrowserInterfaceBroker for the main
frame. The Remote is moved into the response callback so it stays
alive until the browser replies.

For verification only: the callback logs seed[0..3] to stderr so a
smoke test can confirm the channel works end to end. Later patches
(canvas, WebGL, navigator, ...) will instead store the config in a
per-frame holder and read from it during fingerprint surface calls.

Files touched:
- chrome/common/fingerprint.mojom                          (new)
- chrome/common/BUILD.gn                                   (register mojom)
- chrome/browser/fingerprint/fingerprint_profile.{h,cc}    (impl provider)
- chrome/browser/chrome_browser_interface_binders.cc       (register binder)
- chrome/renderer/chrome_render_frame_observer.cc          (fetch + log)

Verified: 'chronium --fingerprint-profile=...' boots, browser logs
'Loaded fingerprint profile from ...' and renderer logs
'fp config received, seed[0..3]=15,58,139,108' matching the JSON seed.
